==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dishonesty
<hw>Dis*hon"es*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. OF.
<ets>deshonest⟦eacute⟧</ets>, F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧shonn⟦ecir⟧tet⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Dishonor; dishonorableness; shame.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
⟦ldquo⟧The hidden things of <xex>dishonesty</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>2 Cor.
iv. 2.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Want of honesty, probity, or integrity in principle;
want of fairness and straightforwardness; a disposition to defraud,
deceive, or betray; faithlessness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Violation of trust or of justice; fraud; any
deviation from probity; a dishonest act.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Lewdness; unchastity.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

